| Timestamp           | TTP   | Detection Status | Notes                         |
| ------------------- | ----- | ---------------- | ----------------------------- |
| 2026-04-10 17:10:12 | T1566 | Detected         | PowerShell execution detected |
| 2026-04-10 17:11:03 | T1566 | Detected         | CMD execution detected        |
| 2026-04-10 17:12:10 | T1566 | Not Detected     | No C2 traffic observed        |

---

## ⚠️ Challenges Faced

* Missing stockpile adversary profiles
* Sandcat payload not generated automatically
* UI issues in Caldera v5
* Dependency conflicts in Kali Linux

---

## ✅ Solutions

* Manual payload compilation using Go
* Custom adversary creation
* Direct API-based agent deployment
* Custom Wazuh rule creation

---

## 🧠 Conclusion

The lab successfully demonstrated adversary emulation and detection using Caldera and Wazuh. While endpoint-level detection was effective, gaps in detecting advanced techniques such as command-and-control communication were identified.

This highlights the importance of continuous rule tuning, improved logging, and correlation for enhancing SOC capabilities.

